<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=748&amp;p=3914#p3914"><![CDATA[
To make the Shutdown item directly shutdown instead of showing the shutdown dialog, go to 'Customize Start Menu' tab in Settings. Locate &quot;ShutdownBoxItem&quot; in the left column and double click it. Change the &quot;Command&quot; from &quot;shutdown_box&quot; to just &quot;shutdown&quot; (or &quot;sleep&quot; or whatever you want).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Jun 20, 2013 9:21 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
